With the Shoreward Revenant gone, the Toll-Marshal of the Three Routes has emerged to enforce simultaneous jurisdiction over all three historical trade routes at the Shoreward approach, blocking access to Mafdet from the Reach. The Toll-Marshal cannot be contested on procedural grounds and has already destroyed two enforcement teams that attempted legal challenge. The Mafdet postmaster has issued a writ of dissolution authorizing lethal force as the only available remediation.
The Toll-Marshal of the Three Routes has been dissolved and the simultaneous jurisdiction block on the Shoreward approach has ended. The three historical trade routes are now accessible through the Threshold. The postmaster has filed the dissolution confirmation with the Mafdet Harbor Authority, which has begun recognizing Warden-issued transit documents for the Tidemouth crossing.
